<p>
<seg id=1> United States president Clinton, on World Aids Day, promised to provide new financial assistance to prevent this fatal disease, including allocating even more funds to research. </seg>
<seg id=2> Clinton plans to increase funding on AIDS research to National Institutes of Health by 30 percent. </seg>
<seg id=3> He is also preparing to announce a 10 million U.S. dollar fund for taking care of AIDS orphans. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Clinton government said this increase in research funding provided by United States public funding is largest one-time increase ever for AIDS research. </seg>
</p>
